00:33:23,542 --> 00:33:24,876
The CIA
did very good warning

518
00:33:24,959 --> 00:33:27,083
in that period of time.

519
00:33:27,167 --> 00:33:29,125
There are dozens
and dozens of reports

520
00:33:29,209 --> 00:33:30,584
in which we express the view

521
00:33:30,667 --> 00:33:34,834
that bin Laden is intending
to attack the United States.

522
00:33:36,334 --> 00:33:38,918
We would have weekly
or biweekly meetings

523
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:40,417
sometimes on exactly

524
00:33:40,500 --> 00:33:41,918
what was going on.

525
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:44,292
It's so frustrating

526
00:33:44,375 --> 00:33:46,459
when you can't figure
out date and time.

527
00:33:46,542 --> 00:33:49,375
There's always
a large band of uncertainty,

528
00:33:49,459 --> 00:33:51,417
and that's fertile ground

529
00:33:51,500 --> 00:33:52,918
for argument.

530
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:55,042
And if you warn
about every little thing,

531
00:33:55,125 --> 00:33:56,292
then you're crying wolf

532
00:33:56,375 --> 00:33:58,000
and nobody pays
attention to you at all.

533
00:33:58,083 --> 00:34:01,250
Middle East,
South Asia, Europe,

534
00:34:01,334 --> 00:34:03,000
United States. Where?

535
00:34:03,083 --> 00:34:05,792
You just don't know.

536
00:34:05,876 --> 00:34:07,584
We did not
at this time

537
00:34:07,667 --> 00:34:08,959
and in this report have

538
00:34:09,042 --> 00:34:10,918
what I would call
"actionable intelligence."

539
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:12,751
"I want to know when,
I want to know where,

540
00:34:12,834 --> 00:34:14,083
I want to know who."

541
00:34:14,167 --> 00:34:16,292
We could not
determine time,

542
00:34:16,375 --> 00:34:17,626
target, and method.

543
00:34:17,709 --> 00:34:19,417
You know, I really
wish I could tell you

544
00:34:19,500 --> 00:34:20,792
when and where.

545
00:34:20,876 --> 00:34:24,792
But it's not that easy with
a clandestine organization.

546
00:34:24,876 --> 00:34:26,834
"Well, if you just had
more human assets and you

547
00:34:26,918 --> 00:34:28,751
"did less analysis,
then we would know

548
00:34:28,834 --> 00:34:30,083
all these things."

549
00:34:30,167 --> 00:34:31,417
Well, that isn't true.

550
00:34:31,500 --> 00:34:34,250
You can say we're pretty
sure it's gonna happen,

551
00:34:34,334 --> 00:34:38,584
but we can't make
that decision to say,

552
00:34:38,667 --> 00:34:40,918
you should do or not do.

553
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:44,667
We can say that
our bottom line is,

554
00:34:44,751 --> 00:34:47,167
"It looks pretty dangerous."

555
00:34:56,042 --> 00:34:57,250
The headline says,

556
00:34:57,334 --> 00:35:00,542
"Bin Laden Determined
to Strike In U.S."

557
00:35:00,626 --> 00:35:02,209
There were just warning
after warning after warning

558
00:35:02,292 --> 00:35:03,500
all spring.

559
00:35:03,584 --> 00:35:06,500
Well, you know with
the benefit of hindsight...

560
00:35:06,584 --> 00:35:08,626
We knew something
huge was gonna happen.

561
00:35:08,709 --> 00:35:10,792
it would seem that this was

562
00:35:10,876 --> 00:35:13,042
a perfect warning

563
00:35:13,125 --> 00:35:15,834
in August of 2001

564
00:35:15,918 --> 00:35:18,125
that the United States
was about to be attacked.

565
00:35:18,209 --> 00:35:20,834
Everybody was
completely tense.

566
00:35:20,918 --> 00:35:22,667
Why didn't we
do something about this?

567
00:35:22,751 --> 00:35:26,751
The language being used
by these guys was like,

568
00:35:26,834 --> 00:35:29,375
"Oh, my God.
What are they gonna do?"

569
00:37:23,500 --> 00:37:25,751
On the morning of 9/11,

570
00:37:25,834 --> 00:37:27,375
I was sitting
in my office.

571
00:37:27,459 --> 00:37:29,667
My office was here.

572
00:37:29,751 --> 00:37:32,584
The office of the group
chief was right next to it.

573
00:37:32,667 --> 00:37:35,083
And I had my door open,
and I looked,

574
00:37:35,167 --> 00:37:36,459
and there was an analyst

575
00:37:36,542 --> 00:37:39,334
running through the row
between the cubicles.

576
00:37:39,417 --> 00:37:42,792
And it was one
of the older analysts.

577
00:37:42,876 --> 00:37:45,125
And you don't see
older analysts running.

578
00:37:45,209 --> 00:37:47,542
I was in Jordan.

579
00:37:47,626 --> 00:37:49,000
I was at the CIA.

580
00:37:49,083 --> 00:37:51,292
9/11, I was in my office at NSA.

581
00:37:51,375 --> 00:37:53,500
I was at the Executive Office
Building of the White House.

582
00:37:53,584 --> 00:37:56,626
I was in the Pentagon
when it got hit.

583
00:37:56,709 --> 00:37:59,834
The first breaking news
was coming in.

584
00:37:59,918 --> 00:38:01,792
Somebody has it
on RealPlayer

585
00:38:01,876 --> 00:38:03,375
on their...at their desk.

586
00:38:03,459 --> 00:38:04,959
The report was saying
there was a small aircraft

587
00:38:05,042 --> 00:38:06,417
that apparently had hit.

588
00:38:06,500 --> 00:38:09,459
Right then, second
plane into the second tower,

589
00:38:09,542 --> 00:38:11,626
and I knew.

590
00:38:11,709 --> 00:38:14,167
There was no doubt in
that office at that moment

591
00:38:14,250 --> 00:38:15,918
that this is what we were
waiting for.

592
00:38:16,000 --> 00:38:17,292
This is it.

593
00:38:17,375 --> 00:38:19,667
That's the words that went
through everybody's mind.

594
00:38:19,751 --> 00:38:21,375
This is it.
This is bin Laden.

595
00:38:21,459 --> 00:38:23,375
"It's an attack,
it's terrorism,

596
00:38:23,459 --> 00:38:24,959
and it's AL-Qaeda."

597
00:38:25,042 --> 00:38:26,209
I knew who they were.

598
00:38:26,292 --> 00:38:27,626
I knew what
their intentions were.

599
00:38:27,709 --> 00:38:30,000
This is it.
They pulled this thing off.

600
00:38:30,083 --> 00:38:31,751
We're going
to battle stations.

601
00:38:31,834 --> 00:38:34,459
And we were all evacuated
after that second plane

602
00:38:34,542 --> 00:38:36,876
went in because we thought
the next one...that is,

603
00:38:36,959 --> 00:38:39,000
the Shanksville plane...
might be headed for us.

604
00:38:39,083 --> 00:38:40,334
It was complete chaos.

605
00:38:40,417 --> 00:38:44,042
The plane flew in
under my office.

606
00:38:44,125 --> 00:38:48,042
My two assistants looked out
the window and saw a 757

607
00:38:48,125 --> 00:38:49,751
fly in under their feet.

608
00:38:49,834 --> 00:38:51,250
The order then went out

609
00:38:51,334 --> 00:38:56,167
for the building
to be evacuated, except

610
00:38:56,250 --> 00:38:57,709
for the counterterrorism
analysts.

611
00:38:57,792 --> 00:39:00,375
We essentially decamped
from the high-rises

612
00:39:00,459 --> 00:39:01,918
and moved on into
the operations center.

613
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:07,959
I said, "Look, chief says
we can't go, but, you know,

614
00:39:08,042 --> 00:39:10,417
if you want to leave,
I'll cover for you."

615
00:39:10,500 --> 00:39:13,000
And not one
of those people left.

616
00:39:25,167 --> 00:39:26,542
19 guys.

617
00:39:26,626 --> 00:39:29,209
Look at their faces
and think

618
00:39:29,292 --> 00:39:33,459
about the tragic,
terrible, consequences.

619
00:39:34,834 --> 00:39:39,459
19. Only 19.

620
00:39:39,542 --> 00:39:41,292
19 representing thousands

621
00:39:41,375 --> 00:39:44,250
who went through training
camps in Afghanistan.

622
00:39:44,334 --> 00:39:47,334
19 representing all those
who were sponsored

623
00:39:47,417 --> 00:39:52,792
and trained and blessed
these young men on that day.

624
00:40:04,834 --> 00:40:06,250
This is where
it gets hard to talk.

625
00:40:08,667 --> 00:40:10,417
I have to say the worst
moment in my life

626
00:40:10,500 --> 00:40:11,792
happened
in about November

627
00:40:11,876 --> 00:40:13,542
because right
after the bombing,

628
00:40:13,626 --> 00:40:16,542
you're just so busy.

629
00:40:16,626 --> 00:40:19,083
And everybody, you know...
cry at home; come to work;

630
00:40:19,167 --> 00:40:20,584
be professional;
do your job;

631
00:40:20,667 --> 00:40:22,083
go home; cry at home;
come to work;

632
00:40:22,167 --> 00:40:23,375
be professional;
and do your job.

633
00:40:23,459 --> 00:40:25,500
And people were very
focused, running around,

634
00:40:25,584 --> 00:40:27,042
getting the job done.

635
00:40:27,125 --> 00:40:28,834
On about November,
things started

636
00:40:28,918 --> 00:40:30,459
to slow down
a little bit,

637
00:40:30,542 --> 00:40:32,000
and the guilt sets in.

638
00:40:32,083 --> 00:40:33,542
And that is
just the worst.

639
00:40:33,626 --> 00:40:35,417
I'm sorry.
I'm gonna cry now.

640
00:40:35,500 --> 00:40:37,167
Um...

641
00:40:38,876 --> 00:40:41,125
feeling like you wish you
could have done something,

642
00:40:41,209 --> 00:40:42,959
but especially
when all the criticism

643
00:40:43,042 --> 00:40:44,459
starts to come in.

644
00:40:44,542 --> 00:40:46,000
People would say things
in Congress like,

645
00:40:46,083 --> 00:40:47,584
"You were negligent."

646
00:40:47,667 --> 00:40:48,959
I was like, "Really?

647
00:40:49,042 --> 00:40:50,918
"What did you know about
bin Laden before 2001?

648
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:53,292
"Nothing! You didn't
help us at all.

649
00:40:53,375 --> 00:40:56,417
And now you're blaming
us for having tried..."

650
00:40:56,500 --> 00:40:59,292
This is not a matter of scapegoating.

651
00:40:59,375 --> 00:41:01,334
This is a matter
of accountability.

652
00:41:01,417 --> 00:41:02,751
There has been...

653
00:41:02,834 --> 00:41:04,042
What does the term

654
00:41:04,125 --> 00:41:06,417
"accountability"
mean to you?

655
00:41:06,500 --> 00:41:08,042
Prior to September 11th,

656
00:41:08,125 --> 00:41:09,500
U.S. intelligence officials

657
00:41:09,584 --> 00:41:11,584
possessed
terrorist information

658
00:41:11,667 --> 00:41:15,292
that, if properly handled,
could have disrupted

659
00:41:15,375 --> 00:41:17,209
or possibly prevented
the terrorist attacks.

660
00:41:17,292 --> 00:41:18,417
It seems

661
00:41:18,500 --> 00:41:20,042
from your testimony...

662
00:41:20,125 --> 00:41:21,542
That information was

663
00:41:21,626 --> 00:41:23,125
not distributed to the FBI.

664
00:41:24,792 --> 00:41:28,042
...The CIA analysts

665
00:41:28,125 --> 00:41:29,667
and FBI officials in
the New York field office...

666
00:41:29,751 --> 00:41:31,751
Has anyone in the CIA

667
00:41:31,834 --> 00:41:34,667
been held accountable
for the failures

668
00:41:34,751 --> 00:41:35,959
of September 11th

669
00:41:36,042 --> 00:41:38,459
or the events
leading up to it?

670
00:41:52,375 --> 00:41:55,876
Jennifer called me
not long after 9/11,

671
00:41:55,959 --> 00:41:57,751
screaming at me
on the phone.

672
00:41:57,834 --> 00:41:59,042
And we were just in...
we were,

673
00:41:59,125 --> 00:42:00,500
a two-second walk
from each other

674
00:42:00,584 --> 00:42:01,751
in different vaults.

675
00:42:01,834 --> 00:42:02,918
But, "You did this.
This is your fault.

676
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:04,292
You didn't report
on..." so-and-so.

677
00:42:04,375 --> 00:42:05,667
Blah-blah-blah-blah-
blah-blah-blah...

678
00:42:05,751 --> 00:42:07,042
And I screamed
back at her

679
00:42:07,125 --> 00:42:08,375
and slammed
the phone down.

680
00:42:08,459 --> 00:42:09,751
And at the time,
I was really angry,

681
00:42:09,834 --> 00:42:12,375
and I actually really
never spoke to her again.

682
00:42:12,459 --> 00:42:13,626
But looking back on it,

683
00:42:13,709 --> 00:42:15,334
I think it's just...
it was just

684
00:42:15,417 --> 00:42:17,417
a manifestation
of her passion

685
00:42:17,500 --> 00:42:21,000
and her sense of...
her own sense of guilt.

686
00:42:22,500 --> 00:42:24,292
I mean,
everybody felt it.

687
00:42:49,209 --> 00:42:53,334
We were told to evacuate Yemen.

688
00:42:53,417 --> 00:42:56,459
The entire team
already boarded the plane,

689
00:42:56,542 --> 00:43:00,125
and I was asked

690
00:43:00,209 --> 00:43:02,250
that I will stay,
I should stay

691
00:43:02,334 --> 00:43:03,876
and to talk to
an individual named

692
00:43:03,959 --> 00:43:07,083
Nasser AL-Bahri...
Abu Jandal.

693
00:43:13,584 --> 00:43:17,500
We showed him
a photo book

694
00:43:17,584 --> 00:43:19,250
that has a lot
of photos in it.

695
00:43:20,626 --> 00:43:22,292
He identified bin Laden,

696
00:43:22,375 --> 00:43:24,125
he identified
Ayman Zawahiri...

697
00:43:24,209 --> 00:43:26,292
He identified
the usual suspects

698
00:43:26,375 --> 00:43:28,459
that there is no way
he would never know.

699
00:43:28,542 --> 00:43:30,918
But he didn't
identify anyone

700
00:43:31,000 --> 00:43:33,918
from the, you know,
second tier.

701
00:43:34,000 --> 00:43:35,209
No one.

702
00:43:35,292 --> 00:43:37,626
And then he closed
the book.

703
00:43:37,709 --> 00:43:39,500
"I don't have
anything else.

704
00:43:39,584 --> 00:43:40,876
Don't know anyone."

705
00:43:40,959 --> 00:43:43,375
So I ask him, "Please.
Can you look at it again?"

706
00:43:43,459 --> 00:43:46,292
But I just said,
"Please. You know,

707
00:43:46,375 --> 00:43:47,417
come on.
Look at it again."

708
00:43:47,500 --> 00:43:49,167
He was annoyed.

709
00:43:49,250 --> 00:43:51,667
He said, "I just did.
There is nothing..."

710
00:43:51,751 --> 00:43:53,542
"For friendship's sake,
you know?

711
00:43:53,626 --> 00:43:55,542
We're now friends..."

712
00:43:55,626 --> 00:43:58,584
So he did. Same thing.

713
00:43:58,667 --> 00:44:01,542
So I laughed.
I went like...

714
00:44:02,626 --> 00:44:04,834
To Bob, I said,
"See? I told you."

715
00:44:04,918 --> 00:44:06,292
"What's goin' on?
What did you tell me?"

716
00:44:06,375 --> 00:44:08,459
"Well, I told Bob...
my friend...I told him

717
00:44:08,542 --> 00:44:12,334
"here...I said that
you're basically faking.

718
00:44:12,417 --> 00:44:14,167
"You're not
cooperating at all.

719
00:44:14,250 --> 00:44:15,834
And I think
I won the bet."

720
00:44:15,918 --> 00:44:17,959
"What are you talking
about? I'm cooperating."

721
00:44:18,042 --> 00:44:20,375
"Come on. Really?
You're cooperating?

722
00:44:20,459 --> 00:44:21,626
"Do you think
I just flew

723
00:44:21,709 --> 00:44:23,792
"all the way from D.C.
to talk to you

724
00:44:23,876 --> 00:44:25,459
"about this kind of
like small talk

725
00:44:25,542 --> 00:44:26,834
"and I don't know
who you are?

726
00:44:26,918 --> 00:44:29,000
I don't know
what you know?"

727
00:44:29,083 --> 00:44:31,542
"This guy,
for example...

728
00:44:31,626 --> 00:44:33,500
"He was in your
guesthouse in 1999.

729
00:44:33,584 --> 00:44:35,751
"He was sick. You were
taking care of him,

730
00:44:35,834 --> 00:44:37,167
"putting soup
on his lips

731
00:44:37,250 --> 00:44:41,417
"and you claim you have
no idea who this guy is?

732
00:44:41,500 --> 00:44:43,083
I know a lot about
your organization."

733
00:44:45,459 --> 00:44:47,292
"Maybe some of these
people in the book are

734
00:44:47,375 --> 00:44:48,584
in my custody."

735
00:44:48,667 --> 00:44:50,626
"Maybe some of
the people in the book

736
00:44:50,709 --> 00:44:52,709
"are friend of mine's.

737
00:44:52,792 --> 00:44:54,709
"Maybe they are
my sources.

738
00:44:54,792 --> 00:44:57,500
"Every time I ask
you a question,

739
00:44:57,584 --> 00:45:00,417
"most probably
I know the answer for.

740
00:45:00,500 --> 00:45:01,876
"And that's how I gauge

741
00:45:01,959 --> 00:45:04,375
"if you're cooperating
or not.

742
00:45:04,459 --> 00:45:07,918
So do you want to start
from the beginning?"

743
00:45:08,000 --> 00:45:09,792
He said, yes.

744
00:45:09,876 --> 00:45:11,876
So we showed him
the book again.

745
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:13,792
He identified almost
everyone in the book

746
00:45:13,876 --> 00:45:15,292
that we know...
we'd assembled...

747
00:45:15,375 --> 00:45:17,125
from the East Africa
Embassy bombing,

748
00:45:17,209 --> 00:45:19,292
from the "USS Cole,"

749
00:45:19,375 --> 00:45:21,584
to include eight
of the hijackers.

750
00:45:21,667 --> 00:45:23,417
And he still insisted
that bin Laden

751
00:45:23,500 --> 00:45:24,626
would never do anything
like this.

752
00:45:24,709 --> 00:45:26,125
And I insisted
that he did.

753
00:45:26,209 --> 00:45:27,459
And I said, "No,
bin Laden did it."

754
00:45:27,542 --> 00:45:28,834
And he said,
"Oh, bin Laden did it?

755
00:45:28,918 --> 00:45:29,918
Who told you?"

756
00:45:30,000 --> 00:45:31,667
"You did."

757
00:45:31,751 --> 00:45:33,876
And he was mad.
He was furious,

758
00:45:33,959 --> 00:45:35,000
because he thought

759
00:45:35,083 --> 00:45:36,375
I was putting words
in his mouth.

760
00:45:36,459 --> 00:45:38,125
I said, "No, you
told me that AL-Qaeda

761
00:45:38,209 --> 00:45:40,167
was behind it,
definitely."

762
00:45:40,250 --> 00:45:42,459
And I took a manila
envelope that I had,

763
00:45:42,542 --> 00:45:45,918
and I put the photos
that he identified

764
00:45:46,000 --> 00:45:48,751
the seven hijackers...
or the eight hijackers...

765
00:45:48,834 --> 00:45:50,125
I put them all
in front of him.

766
00:45:50,209 --> 00:45:51,584
I said, "Do you want to
know who the hijackers?

767
00:45:51,667 --> 00:45:53,375
Those are
the hijackers."

768
00:45:56,083 --> 00:45:59,417
"You told me they
were Qaeda members.

769
00:45:59,500 --> 00:46:01,042
You told me that."

770
00:46:01,125 --> 00:46:03,334
He was in total shock.

771
00:46:03,417 --> 00:46:05,000
He put his hand
like this,

772
00:46:05,083 --> 00:46:06,709
and he starts shaking,

773
00:46:06,792 --> 00:46:09,292
and he asked for,
you know, five minutes.

774
00:46:09,375 --> 00:46:11,042
