00:46:12,459 --> 00:46:15,000
And he said, "I think
the Sheikh went crazy.

777
00:46:15,083 --> 00:46:16,626
What do you want?"

778
00:46:52,000 --> 00:46:54,709
A small group of
people...many of them women...

779
00:46:54,792 --> 00:46:56,542
were blamed.

780
00:46:56,626 --> 00:46:58,125
They were blamed.

781
00:46:58,209 --> 00:47:00,667
"They failed to connect
the dots!"

782
00:47:00,751 --> 00:47:02,042
"Connect the dots."

783
00:47:02,125 --> 00:47:03,167
If I hear that...

784
00:47:03,250 --> 00:47:05,667
The Washington machine
turned on them

785
00:47:05,751 --> 00:47:07,167
and said, "It's your fault."

786
00:47:07,250 --> 00:47:08,792
"Sit and do a line diagram,
where you failed

787
00:47:08,876 --> 00:47:10,167
to connect the dots..."

788
00:47:10,250 --> 00:47:11,500
The dots were there,

789
00:47:11,584 --> 00:47:13,834
It's us who decided to...
we need to erase the dots.

790
00:47:13,918 --> 00:47:16,334
Hello! They're coming at us!

791
00:47:16,417 --> 00:47:19,751
That was...
those were late nights.

792
00:47:19,834 --> 00:47:21,125
You go home, you're driving,

793
00:47:21,209 --> 00:47:23,959
you roll over what
operations are going on,

794
00:47:24,042 --> 00:47:25,918
what threats you
believe are genuine.

795
00:47:26,000 --> 00:47:27,459
You're thinking about your
friends and colleagues

796
00:47:27,542 --> 00:47:28,751
downrange.

797
00:47:28,834 --> 00:47:30,792
Sometimes you're thinking
about some talking head

798
00:47:30,876 --> 00:47:33,751
who launched a bunch
of empty bullets,

799
00:47:33,834 --> 00:47:38,667
you know, of blame trying
to get their face on the TV

800
00:47:38,751 --> 00:47:40,667
and not understanding
the sincerity

801
00:47:40,751 --> 00:47:42,417
of the people involved.

802
00:47:44,042 --> 00:47:46,292
That would cause me
grief the next day

803
00:47:46,375 --> 00:47:48,167
because I knew I was
gonna have to go in

804
00:47:48,250 --> 00:47:50,250
and tell people,
"Listen, they don't

805
00:47:50,334 --> 00:47:52,042
"understand what you do.

806
00:47:52,125 --> 00:47:54,042
"Don't you know that?

807
00:47:54,125 --> 00:47:55,584
Now, let's get it on."

808
00:48:00,959 --> 00:48:04,125
Something that
people don't fully grasp is

809
00:48:04,209 --> 00:48:07,083
how alone the CIA felt
in this period of time.

810
00:48:09,959 --> 00:48:12,792
Just by virtue of
the evolution of events

811
00:48:12,876 --> 00:48:15,459
in history, we ended up
at this moment in time

812
00:48:15,542 --> 00:48:16,918
with kind of
unique knowledge

813
00:48:17,000 --> 00:48:20,042
about this phenomenon,
AL-Qaeda.

814
00:48:20,125 --> 00:48:23,000
I think the feeling
all of us had was,

815
00:48:23,083 --> 00:48:25,292
This is on our shoulders
to prevent this

816
00:48:25,375 --> 00:48:27,375
from ever happening again.

817
00:48:28,834 --> 00:48:31,834
The day of 9/11,
the President pulled us

818
00:48:31,918 --> 00:48:35,667
together and said, "I want
to see a war plan here."

819
00:48:35,751 --> 00:48:39,584
Well, we had been working
on this for a long time.

820
00:48:39,667 --> 00:48:42,250
We were ready to go.

821
00:49:10,626 --> 00:49:12,500
The challenge
when you look at AL-Qaeda

822
00:49:12,584 --> 00:49:14,876
after 9/11 was
to understand it well enough

823
00:49:14,959 --> 00:49:16,626
first to disrupt it
and then dismantle it.

824
00:49:16,709 --> 00:49:19,209
We're not in the business
of disruption alone,

825
00:49:19,292 --> 00:49:20,959
because if you disrupt
an organization,

826
00:49:21,042 --> 00:49:22,542
the adversary's so committed.

827
00:49:22,626 --> 00:49:23,959
I mean, they believe

828
00:49:24,042 --> 00:49:25,792
that what they do is
inspired by a holy book,

829
00:49:25,876 --> 00:49:28,334
that they'll just go on
and plot another attack.

830
00:49:28,417 --> 00:49:29,876
So the business really
became dismantlement:

831
00:49:29,959 --> 00:49:31,125
How do we destroy it?

832
00:49:31,209 --> 00:49:33,042
And that's
a people business.

833
00:49:36,834 --> 00:49:38,918
How do you find
the operators, financiers,

834
00:49:39,000 --> 00:49:40,792
trainers, et cetera?

835
00:49:40,876 --> 00:49:42,542
And how can you know where
they're gonna be tomorrow

836
00:49:42,626 --> 00:49:43,918
so you can pick them up?

837
00:49:46,792 --> 00:49:49,792
The explosion
of intelligence at CIA

838
00:49:49,876 --> 00:49:52,209
after 9/11 is
hard to imagine.

839
00:49:52,292 --> 00:49:54,292
You have a small group
of people in Alec Station

840
00:49:54,375 --> 00:49:56,500
who are looking
at the problem pre-9/11.

841
00:49:56,584 --> 00:50:00,125
They had limited resources.

842
00:50:00,209 --> 00:50:02,876
After 9/11, that small
core group of people

