844
00:50:11,125 --> 00:50:14,876
It was a foundational
change in the organization.

845
00:50:19,542 --> 00:50:22,626
They needed managerial horsepower

846
00:50:22,709 --> 00:50:27,334
to support the increase
in people and budget.

847
00:50:29,042 --> 00:50:31,834
I did not know enough
about AL-Qaeda.

848
00:50:31,918 --> 00:50:34,417
Just what little I had
read in the press.

849
00:50:34,500 --> 00:50:36,125
Was not my specialty.

850
00:50:37,751 --> 00:50:41,375
But, you know,
if you've had 25 years

851
00:50:41,459 --> 00:50:43,584
of experience, you come

852
00:50:43,667 --> 00:50:47,083
with a pretty good sense
of what needs to be done,

853
00:50:47,167 --> 00:50:49,876
even if it's a new
target for you.

854
00:50:49,959 --> 00:50:52,375
Pretty quickly, you learn
what you need to learn

855
00:50:52,459 --> 00:50:54,417
about that target.

856
00:51:02,709 --> 00:51:05,792
I became the head of
the Counterterrorism Center

857
00:51:05,876 --> 00:51:08,667
just about the time
when we were dealing

858
00:51:08,751 --> 00:51:10,584
with all these threats.

859
00:51:10,667 --> 00:51:13,500
I mean, it was daily
constant intelligence

860
00:51:13,584 --> 00:51:17,709
coming about a second wave
of attacks.

861
00:51:17,792 --> 00:51:21,918
But I had a reputation
for building strong teams.

862
00:51:23,667 --> 00:51:25,167
The phone rang.

863
00:51:25,250 --> 00:51:27,125
A senior came on the line,
basically said,

864
00:51:27,209 --> 00:51:29,209
"We need you to come back.

865
00:51:29,292 --> 00:51:31,500
"You know the gravity
of the situation.

866
00:51:31,584 --> 00:51:33,918
You need to come back
and do what you do."

867
00:51:39,083 --> 00:51:45,959
I basically came back
to be the senior manager

868
00:51:46,042 --> 00:51:49,626
for the worldwide effort
against AL-Qaeda.

869
00:51:49,709 --> 00:51:54,125
I had a multidimensional
responsibility.

870
00:51:54,209 --> 00:51:56,125
I had to protect my people,
you know?

871
00:51:57,626 --> 00:51:59,959
We changed the rulebook
a bit.

872
00:52:02,209 --> 00:52:04,042
We were empowered more.

873
00:52:05,542 --> 00:52:07,542
We did things
more aggressive.

874
00:52:11,167 --> 00:52:13,292
"My job is
to kill AL-Qaeda."

875
00:52:15,584 --> 00:52:17,459
"Either get
shoulder-to-shoulder,

876
00:52:17,542 --> 00:52:19,959
get with us,
or get out of our way."

877
00:52:24,834 --> 00:52:27,751
We had
been focusing on capturing

878
00:52:27,834 --> 00:52:29,292
Abu Zubaydah.

879
00:52:33,167 --> 00:52:36,209
He knew who
the leadership was.

880
00:52:36,292 --> 00:52:39,751
He knew their methods
of attack, their targets.

881
00:52:43,834 --> 00:52:46,334
He was the highest level
AL-Qaeda terrorist

882
00:52:46,417 --> 00:52:48,417
that we had ever captured.

883
00:52:54,125 --> 00:52:57,083
When we captured
him in March, he was

884
00:52:57,167 --> 00:52:58,792
severely wounded,

885
00:52:58,876 --> 00:53:01,834
and we knew we had to get
him out of Pakistan.

886
00:53:01,918 --> 00:53:05,167
And in the past, the way
the U.S. had dealt

887
00:53:05,250 --> 00:53:09,209
with issues like this was
to transfer the terrorist

888
00:53:09,292 --> 00:53:12,584
to a friendly country
for interrogation,

889
00:53:12,667 --> 00:53:15,083
but we needed to take
responsibility

890
00:53:15,167 --> 00:53:19,209
for high level terrorists
ourselves.

891
00:53:19,292 --> 00:53:22,209
So we understood
what we had to do.

892
00:53:22,292 --> 00:53:23,751
And we did it.

893
00:53:25,500 --> 00:53:29,375
We took a lot of
bad guys off the streets.

894
00:53:29,459 --> 00:53:33,125
And they got put up...
and it's now public knowledge...

895
00:53:33,209 --> 00:53:35,000
in a nice little, uh...

896
00:53:35,083 --> 00:53:40,792
let's just say...
boutique locations.

897
00:53:51,709 --> 00:53:53,792
Basically you
have two things you have

898
00:53:53,876 --> 00:53:55,292
to bring with you
to an interrogation room,

899
00:53:55,375 --> 00:53:58,250
especially with
individuals like AL-Qaeda.

900
00:53:58,334 --> 00:54:00,334
You have to bring knowledge,

901
00:54:00,417 --> 00:54:03,876
and you have to bring
empathy.

902
00:54:03,959 --> 00:54:05,584
And if you don't have
those two,

903
00:54:05,667 --> 00:54:08,918
I think most probably,
