01:00:47,209 --> 01:00:48,500
maybe even if Afghanistan.

1027
01:00:48,584 --> 01:00:50,167
That's what my favorite
would have been...

1028
01:00:50,250 --> 01:00:52,292
having him in Afghanistan,
because that was

1029
01:00:52,375 --> 01:00:55,542
his spiritual home,
so to speak,

1030
01:00:55,626 --> 01:00:58,500
from the Afghan jihad.

1031
01:00:58,584 --> 01:01:01,751
I was asked,
"Where is bin Laden,"

1032
01:01:01,834 --> 01:01:03,250
all the time.

1033
01:01:06,667 --> 01:01:08,542
When I went to testify
to the Congress,

1034
01:01:08,626 --> 01:01:10,000
the first thing they
wanted to know was,

1035
01:01:10,083 --> 01:01:12,000
"Where is bin Laden?"

1036
01:01:14,626 --> 01:01:16,125
I went to the Oval Office
a number of times.

1037
01:01:16,209 --> 01:01:20,500
I was asked by the president
"Where is bin Laden?"

1038
01:01:22,167 --> 01:01:24,959
Everybody
would ask the same question:

1039
01:01:25,042 --> 01:01:26,292
"Where is bin Laden?"

1040
01:01:26,375 --> 01:01:29,584
It was very frustrating to
basically have to admit

1041
01:01:29,667 --> 01:01:31,751
that you didn't know.

1042
01:01:33,500 --> 01:01:38,459
One time, one of my
colleagues came in to talk

1043
01:01:38,542 --> 01:01:40,876
to me about,
"Where's bin Laden?"

1044
01:01:40,959 --> 01:01:47,000
And I told him, "Look, you
know, I am so tired of this.

1045
01:01:47,083 --> 01:01:50,042
"The next time that
the next person asks me,

1046
01:01:50,125 --> 01:01:51,876
"'Where is bin Laden,'

1047
01:01:51,959 --> 01:01:54,459
"I'm gonna say,
'You know what? Fuck you.

1048
01:01:54,542 --> 01:01:56,709
Fuck you.'"

1049
01:02:00,500 --> 01:02:02,918
And later that day,
I went home.

1050
01:02:03,000 --> 01:02:05,667
And the first thing my wife
asked me when I get home is,

1051
01:02:05,751 --> 01:02:10,292
"Where is bin Laden?
And why can't you find him?"

1052
01:02:17,167 --> 01:02:19,751
The toughest
position to be in AL-Qaeda

1053
01:02:19,834 --> 01:02:21,209
then was number three,
number four.

1054
01:02:21,292 --> 01:02:22,918
Because why?
You had to communicate.

1055
01:02:23,000 --> 01:02:24,375
You had to communicate
to get attacks done.

1056
01:02:24,459 --> 01:02:25,959
You had to communicate...
and if you were doing that,

1057
01:02:26,042 --> 01:02:28,083
we're on you.

1058
01:02:28,167 --> 01:02:30,876
Frankly, even though

1059
01:02:30,959 --> 01:02:33,417
in the back of our minds,
we knew we had

1060
01:02:33,500 --> 01:02:35,000
to get him some day,

1061
01:02:35,083 --> 01:02:38,667
we were actually
too busy going after those

1062
01:02:38,751 --> 01:02:40,792
who were actually
plotting against us.

1063
01:02:43,834 --> 01:02:45,709
Congratulations,
Abu Butthead.

1064
01:02:45,792 --> 01:02:47,209
You're now number three
in AL-Qaeda.

1065
01:02:47,292 --> 01:02:48,834
That's the good news.
The bad news is,

1066
01:02:48,918 --> 01:02:50,500
you're now number
three in AL-Qaeda.

1067
01:02:50,584 --> 01:02:52,000
You'd better buckle
your chinstrap

1068
01:02:52,083 --> 01:02:53,542
because your
career path is

1069
01:02:53,626 --> 01:02:55,167
probably going
to be short-lived.

1070
01:03:00,000 --> 01:03:01,667
There is an aspect
of the intelligence business

1071
01:03:01,751 --> 01:03:03,000
called targeting.

1072
01:03:03,083 --> 01:03:06,083
I think this is a revolution
for a couple of reasons.

1073
01:03:06,167 --> 01:03:08,876
Just in the past ten years,
the agency

1074
01:03:08,959 --> 01:03:10,834
has transitioned
from strategic intelligence

1075
01:03:10,918 --> 01:03:14,125
to tactical intelligence
that helps you identify

1076
01:03:14,209 --> 01:03:18,542
the movements and locations
of one specific individual.

1077
01:03:18,626 --> 01:03:21,042
I'm not just worried about
what AL-Qaeda

1078
01:03:21,125 --> 01:03:22,626
looks like strategically;

1079
01:03:22,709 --> 01:03:24,334
I want an analyst

1080
01:03:24,417 --> 01:03:26,459
who's spending
all their time looking

1081
01:03:26,542 --> 01:03:28,751
at one target
with one name...

1082
01:03:30,250 --> 01:03:32,375
and people
whose whole goal in life

1083
01:03:32,459 --> 01:03:34,959
is following
one human being.

1084
01:03:47,709 --> 01:03:50,209
I went to the other women
who had become

1085
01:03:50,292 --> 01:03:52,542
targeting officers
when I moved over...

1086
01:03:52,626 --> 01:03:55,125
Jennifer Matthews
and some of the other women

1087
01:03:55,209 --> 01:03:56,584
who had already paved
the way...

1088
01:03:56,667 --> 01:03:58,083
just to ask them,
"How do I do this?

1089
01:03:58,167 --> 01:04:00,751
I have to build this
from the ground up,"

1090
01:04:00,834 --> 01:04:03,500
kind of like they did
on the bin Laden side.

1091
01:04:03,584 --> 01:04:05,918
You know,
"How do I do this?"

1092
01:04:06,000 --> 01:04:09,125
We still didn't have a great
technical tool to do that.

1093
01:04:09,209 --> 01:04:10,918
I built a spreadsheet.

1094
01:04:11,000 --> 01:04:14,250
And when I reached out
to Barbara and Gina

1095
01:04:14,334 --> 01:04:15,918
and a few other women,
they just said,

1096
01:04:16,000 --> 01:04:17,626
"That's how we do it.

1097
01:04:17,709 --> 01:04:20,334
Go for it. That's exactly
how you get it done."

1098
01:04:25,542 --> 01:04:27,584
You're leaving
a digital trail every day.

1099
01:04:27,667 --> 01:04:28,959
So are terrorists...

1100
01:04:29,042 --> 01:04:30,209
when that person travels,

1101
01:04:30,292 --> 01:04:32,250
when that person
gets on a phone,

1102
01:04:32,334 --> 01:04:35,292
when we get information
from a courier in AL-Qaeda

1103
01:04:35,375 --> 01:04:36,584
about who he's touching

1104
01:04:36,667 --> 01:04:39,083
and we bounce it against
information we might have

1105
01:04:39,167 --> 01:04:41,209
found out two years ago.

1106
01:04:42,876 --> 01:04:45,125
They're looking at
a human terrorist in a field

1107
01:04:45,209 --> 01:04:47,417
and they might send
a cable to a station

1108
01:04:47,500 --> 01:04:49,459
that results in action
against that target

1109
01:04:49,542 --> 01:04:51,292
the next day.

1110
01:04:55,250 --> 01:04:56,959
Somebody who wants
in the fight.

1111
01:04:57,042 --> 01:05:00,083
That's what a targeter is.

1112
01:05:00,167 --> 01:05:03,209
You have to intimately know
the target

1113
01:05:03,292 --> 01:05:04,584
that you're going after,

1114
01:05:04,667 --> 01:05:07,751
how you think that person
is gonna act, react,

1115
01:05:07,834 --> 01:05:09,167
what they're gonna do
that day,

1116
01:05:09,250 --> 01:05:11,918
what their strategy is,
who they're gonna talk to.

1117
01:05:12,000 --> 01:05:13,375
What are their
priorities in life?

1118
01:05:13,459 --> 01:05:15,667
Is it wife number one,
is it wife number two?

1119
01:05:52,083 --> 01:05:55,834
I was in Baghdad shortly
after the war started,

1120
01:05:55,918 --> 01:06:00,083
and it was kind of like
being in the Wild West.

1121
01:06:01,876 --> 01:06:03,918
It was complete chaos.

1122
01:06:13,709 --> 01:06:15,709
Bin Laden was initially
excited about this.

1123
01:06:15,792 --> 01:06:17,334
He was excited about Iraq.

1124
01:06:17,417 --> 01:06:18,751
This is something he

1125
01:06:18,834 --> 01:06:20,792
couldn't, at the time,
pull off.

1126
01:06:20,876 --> 01:06:23,626
So he was happy
to support the endeavor.

1127
01:06:41,000 --> 01:06:43,459
He was such
a brutal terrorist.

1128
01:06:45,167 --> 01:06:48,709
I just felt like we owed
it to the people of Iraq

1129
01:06:48,792 --> 01:06:50,667
to remove him.

1130
01:06:56,709 --> 01:07:00,000
It seems so strange
that I never met Zarqawi.

1131
01:07:00,083 --> 01:07:02,042
My former colleagues

1132
01:07:02,125 --> 01:07:03,959
in the Jordanian
Intelligence Service

1133
01:07:04,042 --> 01:07:05,751
used to call him
my boyfriend.

1134
01:07:14,751 --> 01:07:17,542
I felt like I knew Zarqawi too well.

1135
01:07:26,792 --> 01:07:29,042
He was a quiet guy...

1136
01:07:30,542 --> 01:07:32,375
in a pathological
sort of way.

1137
01:07:32,459 --> 01:07:34,792
I mean, he was a monster.

1138
01:07:37,209 --> 01:07:39,751
There were calls at
2:00, 3:00 in the morning

1139
01:07:39,834 --> 01:07:40,918
from the group chief

1140
01:07:41,000 --> 01:07:42,334
every time a bombing
happened,

1141
01:07:42,417 --> 01:07:43,626
every time
he set off a VBID,

1142
01:07:43,709 --> 01:07:46,792
every time he targeted
a mosque or anything.

1143
01:07:49,709 --> 01:07:52,584
You know, I was
thinking about him 24/7,

1144
01:07:52,667 --> 01:07:57,876
and it just wasn't
pleasant after a while.

1145
01:07:59,834 --> 01:08:03,292
The model
to me is very clear.

1146
01:08:03,375 --> 01:08:06,042
Our special forces,
our JSOC operators,

1147
01:08:06,125 --> 01:08:07,542
their analysts,
our analysts,

1148
01:08:07,626 --> 01:08:09,334
their operators,
our operators,

1149
01:08:09,417 --> 01:08:11,000
were working hand-in-hand.

1150
01:08:11,083 --> 01:08:12,584
They were downrange.

1151
01:08:12,667 --> 01:08:15,000
They were downrange
in our field stations

1152
01:08:15,083 --> 01:08:16,584
assisting in operations,

1153
01:08:16,667 --> 01:08:18,751
bringing that expertise
there.

1154
01:08:18,834 --> 01:08:22,959
And the lessons
and the ability to take

1155
01:08:23,042 --> 01:08:24,459
intelligence operations
combined

1156
01:08:24,542 --> 01:08:29,000
with special operations
to create a synergy,

1157
01:08:29,083 --> 01:08:30,334
a deadly synergy.

1158
01:08:30,417 --> 01:08:34,042
And your job
as a targeting officer

1159
01:08:34,125 --> 01:08:36,626
in a war theater
is to help point

1160
01:08:36,709 --> 01:08:39,292
boots on the ground
or something up above

1161
01:08:39,375 --> 01:08:43,042
toward a target and be
as accurate as possible.

1162
01:08:50,250 --> 01:08:53,667
Wait!

1163
01:08:53,751 --> 01:08:55,417
For me, war is sort of like

1164
01:08:55,500 --> 01:08:57,792
something radioactive
that you shouldn't touch

1165
01:08:57,876 --> 01:08:59,918
unless you've done
a tremendous amount

1166
01:09:00,000 --> 01:09:02,542
of understanding of just
the damage that it will do.

1167
01:09:14,250 --> 01:09:17,334
You can flirt with the idea
that "I can cross the line

1168
01:09:17,417 --> 01:09:20,417
"and go into the dark side
and then I can walk back

1169
01:09:20,500 --> 01:09:23,042
"because I'm going
in the dark side

1170
01:09:23,125 --> 01:09:25,000
for a good purpose."

1171
01:09:25,083 --> 01:09:27,709
And there are times when
that may be appropriate,

1172
01:09:27,792 --> 01:09:30,083
but it is dangerous.

1173
01:09:32,042 --> 01:09:34,292
It's easier next time
to cross.

1174
01:09:59,792 --> 01:10:01,334
I did not like being
on the raids.

1175
01:10:01,417 --> 01:10:04,959
That wasn't...I was
an analyst.

1176
01:10:05,042 --> 01:10:08,375
Wasn't...I just didn't...I...

1177
01:10:14,375 --> 01:10:16,417
I think there are
questions

1178
01:10:16,500 --> 01:10:18,167
about an intelligence
organization

1179
01:10:18,250 --> 01:10:21,500
that slowly gets involved
in executing these types

1180
01:10:21,584 --> 01:10:23,542
of global counterterrorism
operations.

1181
01:10:23,626 --> 01:10:25,334
That's a real
mind-set change.

1182
01:10:25,417 --> 01:10:28,667
The war was not
an agnostic video game.

1183
01:10:28,751 --> 01:10:30,167
It was a personal game
where you know

1184
01:10:30,250 --> 01:10:31,334
you're responsible

1185
01:10:31,417 --> 01:10:32,918
not only for the lives
of Americans,

1186
01:10:33,000 --> 01:10:35,042
but for going up
against an adversary

1187
01:10:35,125 --> 01:10:36,667
that you got to kill
or capture.

1188
01:10:36,751 --> 01:10:39,876
August of 2004,
I think we did 18 raids

1189
01:10:39,959 --> 01:10:41,459
that month in Iraq,

1190
01:10:41,542 --> 01:10:42,876
our force.

1191
01:10:42,959 --> 01:10:46,083
Two years later in 2006,
same month,

1192
01:10:46,167 --> 01:10:48,250
Iraq, also,
we did 300 raids.

1193
01:10:50,709 --> 01:10:52,334
Our ability to collect

1194
01:10:52,417 --> 01:10:53,918
intelligence,
act on intelligence,

1195
01:10:54,000 --> 01:10:55,709
and then collect more
intelligence had taken

1196
01:10:55,792 --> 01:11:00,918
an almost industrial
size and speed to it.

1197
01:11:05,542 --> 01:11:07,918
It was definitely
a well-oiled machine.

1198
01:11:08,000 --> 01:11:10,334
There were rolling raids.

1199
01:11:10,417 --> 01:11:13,584
Sometimes
those were fruitful,

1200
01:11:13,667 --> 01:11:14,959
and sometimes not so much.

1201
01:11:15,042 --> 01:11:16,375
I think
sometimes the momentum

1202
01:11:16,459 --> 01:11:18,959
sort of overtook
the substance

1203
01:11:19,042 --> 01:11:20,542
of what we were going after.

1204
01:11:20,626 --> 01:11:21,876
You know, it's like,
"There's another target.

1205
01:11:21,959 --> 01:11:26,083
Let's go after it,
just because we can."

1206
01:11:26,167 --> 01:11:27,792
The machine just kept going.

1207
01:11:31,959 --> 01:11:34,459
We had executed thousands

1208
01:11:34,542 --> 01:11:36,959
of these kinds of raids
in Iraq

1209
01:11:37,042 --> 01:11:38,375
and Afghanistan,

1210
01:11:38,459 --> 01:11:41,000
and we got better
and better at them.

1211
01:11:41,083 --> 01:11:48,209
So it was that evolution
in particular with the CIA

1212
01:11:48,292 --> 01:11:50,792
in ways that we
just couldn't have imagined

1213
01:11:50,876 --> 01:11:54,834
in 2001 or 2002,

1214
01:11:54,918 --> 01:11:57,709
but were absolutely
critical, as it turns out,

1215
01:11:57,792 --> 01:12:00,292
in order to be able
to meet this threat.

1216
01:12:02,209 --> 01:12:04,042
But you
definitely need to know

1217
01:12:04,125 --> 01:12:07,375
what your moral center is
and how you define that

1218
01:12:07,459 --> 01:12:10,417
for yourself in order
to be able to do that job.

1219
01:12:10,500 --> 01:12:13,959
I mean, I worked in a center
where my job was to hunt

1220
01:12:14,042 --> 01:12:16,083
a person down
to capture or kill.

1221
01:12:16,167 --> 01:12:17,626
I mean, I had to be
OK with that.

1222
01:12:17,709 --> 01:12:21,125
And, you know, the paradox
of wanting to save

1223
01:12:21,209 --> 01:12:22,709
the women and children
of Iraq

1224
01:12:22,792 --> 01:12:26,375
and kill someone
in order to do that

1225
01:12:26,459 --> 01:12:28,834
wasn't lost on me
by any means.

1226
01:12:28,918 --> 01:12:30,709
But, you know, I...

1227
01:12:30,792 --> 01:12:32,876
I can justify that
for myself.

1228
01:12:37,500 --> 01:12:39,500
The war on terror.

1229
01:12:41,500 --> 01:12:43,500
How can you have
a war on terror

1230
01:12:43,584 --> 01:12:45,709
when terrorism is a tactic?

1231
01:12:45,792 --> 01:12:47,292
You have a war
against people.

1232
01:12:50,125 --> 01:12:53,334
So the question
immediately becomes,

1233
01:12:53,417 --> 01:12:54,876
Who are the people
that we're fighting

1234
01:12:54,959 --> 01:12:56,918
the war against?

1235
01:13:00,042 --> 01:13:03,250
And I think still most
people don't understand

1236
01:13:03,334 --> 01:13:04,667
why they hate us.

1237
01:13:11,751 --> 01:13:15,959
Some strikes are necessary,
but if our solution

1238
01:13:16,042 --> 01:13:19,959
to this kind of problem is
to just strike

1239
01:13:20,042 --> 01:13:22,209
without trying to take
effective efforts

1240
01:13:22,292 --> 01:13:25,375
to prevent the rise of
threats, it's endless.

1241
01:13:26,876 --> 01:13:29,292
Shock and awe does
not end wars on terrorism.

1242
01:13:29,375 --> 01:13:32,542
It only creates
more terrorism.

1243
01:13:32,626 --> 01:13:34,959
Money starts to flow
to terrorist groups,

1244
01:13:35,042 --> 01:13:37,042
people become
more radicalized.

1245
01:13:40,167 --> 01:13:41,709
Wars on terror
should be fought

1246
01:13:41,792 --> 01:13:45,500
under the radar,
as quietly as possible.

1247
01:13:46,959 --> 01:13:49,959
But counterterrorist
operations are,

1248
01:13:50,042 --> 01:13:51,334
by their nature,

1249
01:13:51,417 --> 01:13:54,417
not very satisfying
to a frightened public.

1250
01:14:05,667 --> 01:14:07,459
And we were working closely

1251
01:14:07,542 --> 01:14:09,542
with the bin Laden unit,

1252
01:14:09,626 --> 01:14:11,792
and the dynamic of
the relationship

1253
01:14:11,876 --> 01:14:13,876
between Zarqawi
and core AL-Qaeda

1254
01:14:13,959 --> 01:14:15,834
sort of turned a lot
of assessments on

1255
01:14:15,918 --> 01:14:18,626
what was happening with
core AL-Qaeda on its head.

1256
01:14:19,876 --> 01:14:22,459
Bin Laden didn't know,
I'm sure, what he was

1257
01:14:22,542 --> 01:14:24,000
getting into with Zarqawi...

1258
01:14:24,083 --> 01:14:26,167
how fundamentally
different he was

1259
01:14:26,250 --> 01:14:28,626
from some of his
other AL-Qaeda leaders.

1260
01:14:30,125 --> 01:14:33,167
He did not have the same
academic background

1261
01:14:33,250 --> 01:14:35,542
that a lot of
the AL-Qaeda scholars had.

1262
01:14:35,626 --> 01:14:37,959
He didn't have the same...

1263
01:14:38,042 --> 01:14:41,459
for a lack of a better way
to put it...

1264
01:14:41,542 --> 01:14:45,250
professional sense
of jihad as AL-Qaeda did.

1265
01:14:45,334 --> 01:14:47,542
He didn't understand
the rules of the game.

1266
01:14:47,626 --> 01:14:50,042
He just thought
he could enact

1267
01:14:50,125 --> 01:14:52,834
any strategy regardless
of how brutal it was.

1268
01:15:19,959 --> 01:15:21,626
It was surprising
to hear

1269
01:15:21,709 --> 01:15:24,459
that Zarqawi was not
being deferential.

1270
01:15:26,459 --> 01:15:28,751
He was being insubordinate.

1271
01:15:47,250 --> 01:15:51,500
Hassan Ghul was
an emissary from AL-Qaeda.

1272
01:15:54,209 --> 01:15:56,876
He was actually
bringing over another letter

1273
01:15:56,959 --> 01:16:00,459
from AL-Qaeda central
to Zarqawi about

1274
01:16:00,542 --> 01:16:03,083
how he should be conducting
operations in Iraq.

1275
